data.name: Study Software Development with Mission Ready
data.summary: At Mission Ready you will learn how to create responsive mobile-first web applications and be confident problem solver using code. If you are a hands-on creator and enjoy making, testing and seeing your creations come to life, then a career in full-stack and software development is for you.

data.name: Full Stack Developer
data.summary: A full stack web developer is a person who can develop both client and server software

data.name: Study UX Design with Mission Ready
data.summary: At Mission Ready you will learn how to combine technology, design, market research, psychology & business; and be confident at designing tech products & solutions; and meet inspiring industry mentors and speakers. If you enjoy understanding what makes humans tick and have a high level of empathy for people and their technology journey, then a career in UX design is for you.

data.name: UX Designer
data.summary: The UX designer role is to make a product or service usable, enjoyable, and accessible. While many companies design user experiences, the term is most often associated with digital design for websites and apps.

data.name: Junior Investment Banker
data.summary: This is a common first role in the field of investment banking. You will work long hours and learn the fundamentals of what it takes to be an investment banker. See current seek.co.nz listings below.

data.name: Private Equity Associate
data.summary: An Associate's job is to lead deal processes from start to finish - raising capital, acquiring companies, improving companies, and selling companies.
